Package com.camerontec.util.concurrent.pool

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CheckedOutContext
    Interface representing a context supplied to a PoolableSharedObject when it is checked out so that it may be checked back in later.
    ConcurrentSharedObjectPool<E extends PoolableSharedObject>
    Interface to be implemented by object pools designed for concurrent use.
    PoolableSharedObject
    Interface to be implemented by shared objects capable of being pooled in a SingleAcquirerConcurrentSharedObjectPool.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConcurrentSharedObjectPoolCheckedOutContext<E extends PoolableSharedObject>
    Checked out context for shared objects originating from a SingleAcquirerConcurrentSharedObjectPool.
    MultiAcquirerConcurrentSharedObjectPool<E extends PoolableSharedObject>
    Shared object pool implementation which has the following characteristics: Fixed size Only one thread may ever MultiAcquirerConcurrentSharedObjectPool.checkIn(PoolableSharedObject) check in} objects to the pool (typically this would be the pool owner). Any thread may check out objects from the pool.
    SingleAcquirerConcurrentSharedObjectPool<E extends PoolableSharedObject>
    Shared object pool implementation which has the following characteristics: Fixed size Only one thread may ever check out objects from the pool (typically this would be the pool owner). Any thread may check in objects to the pool.
